node.text: and as the summer fades away nothing gold can stay
these boots were made for walkin’
picture yourself in a boat on a river / with tangerine trees and marmalade skies
do you know what that’s worth?
a love letter to my pink haired self:

tachicardia e poesia
addò sta scritto c’aggia suffrì
you should see me in a crown
i see sunshine ‘cause i know that you are mine

come 
d’autunno
sugli alberi 
le foglie
“of those immortal dead who live again/ in minds made better by their presence”
i thought that love was a kind of emptiness
